{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3036172,"name":"Luis Fer","username":"Luis_Fer","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/l/919ad9/{size}.png","created_at":"2022-04-03T22:58:58.372Z","cooked":"<p>Hi, we are trying to auto align our robot using the difference of angle that the limelight provides, we tried using the Rio PID but it was kinda hard to tune because whenever the difference of angle was short, the pid is overshooting a bit.</p>
<p>Then we tried to use motion magic(we are using falcon 500 for our drivetrain) but the problem is that the motors are not moving, something weird is that when i try to move them manually, the motors are coming back to the 0 position.</p>
<p>Does anyone know a better solution to auto align the robot or how to fix the motion magic problem?</p>
<p>Here is the code:<br>
